00:16:32,208 --> 00:16:34,574
I hope she's single
'cause I don't do break-ups.

241
00:16:34,710 --> 00:16:36,678
Hi. Thank you for seeing me.

242
00:16:36,779 --> 00:16:40,237
Yeah, no.
I mean, she just got out of a relationship.

243
00:16:40,716 --> 00:16:43,742
Is that a problem?
Because if it is, that's fine.

244
00:16:43,886 --> 00:16:46,184
I'm a little uncomfortable with this anyway.

245
00:16:46,288 --> 00:16:50,520
Definitely been hurt a lot.
I had a lot of bad experiences.

246
00:16:50,626 --> 00:16:54,084
Some good ones.
But definitely a lot of bad ones.

247
00:16:54,797 --> 00:16:58,893
I'm desperate, basically.
I mean, not in general, you understand?

248
00:16:59,034 --> 00:17:02,731
You know, not just for anybody.
But, man, for her... Yeah.

249
00:17:03,205 --> 00:17:05,571
Why don't you tell me about her?

250
00:17:06,709 --> 00:17:08,836
Let's see, what can I say?

251
00:17:09,144 --> 00:17:12,841
My company handles her finances.
I'm her tax consultant.

252
00:17:13,382 --> 00:17:16,681
Well, I'm one of them.
I'm the junior man on the account.

253
00:17:16,785 --> 00:17:19,219
- So does she know you're interested?
- No.

254
00:17:23,392 --> 00:17:24,552
Alive?

255
00:17:25,628 --> 00:17:27,095
I lent her my pen once.

256
00:17:27,596 --> 00:17:29,894
Shoot. Does anyone have a pen?

257
00:17:30,032 --> 00:17:33,524
- Here, take mine.
- Albert, you're crushing my arm.

258
00:17:33,636 --> 00:17:36,161
Sorry about that. Here you go, Allegra.

259
00:17:39,375 --> 00:17:42,071
Allegra? As in Allegra Cole?

260
00:17:42,211 --> 00:17:44,941
Yeah, I realize that I'm not her usual type.

261
00:17:45,080 --> 00:17:48,880
Well, her last boyfriend owned Sweden
or something.

262
00:17:48,984 --> 00:17:50,713
And that guy was a bum.

263
00:17:50,819 --> 00:17:53,879
He didn't seem like
a very nice person to me.

264
00:17:54,924 --> 00:17:56,949
You swing for the fence.

265
00:17:57,126 --> 00:18:00,527
Look, you don't think I tried
talking myself out of this?

266
00:18:00,629 --> 00:18:04,463
I mean, you don't think I know
how ridiculous this is? I know, okay?

267
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:08,036
I just thought that maybe with your help...

268
00:18:10,105 --> 00:18:14,098
You know what?
I'm really sorry I wasted your time.

269
00:18:25,521 --> 00:18:27,580
Hold on a second, Albert.

270
00:18:30,125 --> 00:18:34,221
You know what it's like
getting up every morning feeling hopeless?

271
00:18:34,430 --> 00:18:37,922
Feeling like the love of your life
is waking up with the wrong man?

272
00:18:38,033 --> 00:18:42,936
But at the same time,
hoping that she still finds happiness...

273
00:18:43,439 --> 00:18:46,272
even if it's never gonna be with you?

274
00:18:47,643 --> 00:18:50,441
You are flat-out...

275
00:18:51,313 --> 00:18:54,476
out of your mind. You know that?

276
00:18:58,387 --> 00:18:59,820
That's good.

277
00:19:00,956 --> 00:19:02,116
It is?

278
00:19:03,058 --> 00:19:05,424
You ever heard of Michelangelo?

279
00:19:05,527 --> 00:19:07,757
Heard of the Sistine Chapel?

280
00:19:09,298 --> 00:19:10,765
Michelangelo.

281
00:19:11,700 --> 00:19:13,258
Sistine Chapel.

282
00:19:13,502 --> 00:19:15,265
You saying you can do this?

283
00:19:15,371 --> 00:19:18,932
My name is Alex Hitchens.
Let's go paint that ceiling.

284
00:19:48,437 --> 00:19:49,904
Take it easy.

285
00:19:51,273 --> 00:19:52,706
Oh, my God!

286
00:20:38,587 --> 00:20:41,112
Well, it looks like I'm still rich.

287
00:20:44,760 --> 00:20:49,094
But what I would really like,
and what I was wondering is...

288
00:20:50,399 --> 00:20:54,460
if I could have $500,000
to invest on my own.

289
00:20:56,472 --> 00:21:00,568
And what were you thinking
of investing in, Allegra?

290
00:21:02,077 --> 00:21:06,707
Well, it's something
that I really have a passion for.

291
00:21:12,788 --> 00:21:15,120
Daydreams are for private time.

292
00:21:15,457 --> 00:21:17,721
When you're in the room, be in the room.

293
00:21:17,826 --> 00:21:21,455
Concentrate. Focus.
Women respond when you respond to them.

294
00:21:21,663 --> 00:21:24,496
My friend Maggie is a talented designer.

295
00:21:24,933 --> 00:21:29,267
I've seen the business plan
and the samples look fantastic.

296
00:21:30,305 --> 00:21:34,401
And I would really like to get involved.

297
00:21:39,014 --> 00:21:40,675
I'll tell you what.

298
00:21:40,816 --> 00:21:45,480
Let us come up with a range of investments
that we think you might be interested in...

299
00:21:45,621 --> 00:21:49,216
and next month,
we'll run the whole lot of them by you.

300
00:21:52,327 --> 00:21:53,316
Okay.

301
00:21:53,462 --> 00:21:55,953
Fine. Thank you. All right, gentlemen.

302
00:21:56,498 --> 00:21:59,092
Let's go over this one more time.
What is the objective?

303
00:21:59,201 --> 00:22:00,634
Shock and awe.

304
00:22:00,769 --> 00:22:03,636
That was shockingly awful.
What is the objective?

305
00:22:03,772 --> 00:22:04,932
Shock and awe.

306
00:22:05,040 --> 00:22:07,406
What is the objective?

307
00:22:08,210 --> 00:22:11,008
- Excuse me, sir.
- Yes, Albert?

308
00:22:18,620 --> 00:22:21,919
I don't really agree with that.

309
00:22:22,024 --> 00:22:24,515
You don't really agree with what?

310
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:34,601
I think if you want to invest $500,000
in your friend's business...

311
00:22:34,703 --> 00:22:36,193
that's exactly what you should do.

312
00:22:36,338 --> 00:22:39,136
You don't need us to tell you what to do.

313
00:22:39,241 --> 00:22:42,301
We're a board of advisers,
not your kindergarten teachers.

314
00:22:42,411 --> 00:22:44,641
If you want to be taken seriously
as an adult...

315
00:22:44,746 --> 00:22:47,112
then start taking yourself seriously
as an adult...

316
00:22:47,216 --> 00:22:50,185
instead of asking for permission
to invest your own money...

317
00:22:50,319 --> 00:22:53,015
from a boardroom
full of your daddy's golf buddies.

318
00:22:53,155 --> 00:22:54,884
- That's quite enough!
- I'm not finished.

319
00:22:55,023 --> 00:22:59,221
I'd like to see anybody in this room
handle the attention and publicity...

320
00:22:59,361 --> 00:23:03,024
that she's had to deal with her whole life,
with half her class.

321
00:23:05,334 --> 00:23:09,464
We should be taking advice from you,
Miss Cole. Not the other way around.

322
00:23:09,571 --> 00:23:12,335
- Sit down...
- No! You know what? I quit!

323
00:23:22,718 --> 00:23:24,083
Oh, my God.

324
00:23:34,229 --> 00:23:36,925
Just breathe. How'd it go?

325
00:23:37,065 --> 00:23:40,592
I yelled at her. I screamed at my boss!
I quit my job!

326
00:23:41,136 --> 00:23:42,899
- What?
- You said...

327
00:23:43,272 --> 00:23:45,832
- I gotta go back.
- No, I didn't tell you to quit.

328
00:23:45,941 --> 00:23:47,704
Relax. Okay, listen, we're fine.

329
00:23:47,809 --> 00:23:50,277
- Would you let me go?
- Albert, no!

330
00:23:51,647 --> 00:23:54,514
Just relax! Okay?

331
00:23:55,050 --> 00:23:58,417
- Just let it marinate for a second. Trust me.
- No!

332
00:24:08,730 --> 00:24:10,755
Relax.

333
00:24:10,899 --> 00:24:13,026
- It's Allegra Cole.
- Answer it.

334
00:24:13,135 --> 00:24:16,696
- Could I speak to you a second?
- Answer the door, Albert.

335
00:24:21,143 --> 00:24:22,405
Yes. Hi.

336
00:24:23,178 --> 00:24:24,577
What's up?

337
00:24:24,913 --> 00:24:26,813
Listen, Albert, right?

338
00:24:27,649 --> 00:24:32,586
- People don't usually talk to me like that.
- Close your mouth, man.

339
00:24:32,688 --> 00:24:35,282
Let me rephrase that.

340
00:24:35,424 --> 00:24:38,257
People never talk to me like that.

341
00:24:39,861 --> 00:24:41,055
Stand up.

342
00:24:41,163 --> 00:24:43,927
I guess it's kind of scary for them.

343
00:24:44,766 --> 00:24:48,634
But that's why I really appreciate
what you did in there.

344
00:24:50,038 --> 00:24:51,938
But I was wondering...

345
00:24:52,040 --> 00:24:56,272
do you think that you and I could
get together sometime this week?

346
00:24:58,347 --> 00:25:01,009
You know, to go over things.

347
00:25:01,984 --> 00:25:03,747
Financial things.

348
00:25:03,852 --> 00:25:07,982
I'd like to see the areas
where I can afford to take some risks.

349
00:25:08,123 --> 00:25:10,455
- Check your schedule.
- I'll check my schedule.

350
00:25:10,559 --> 00:25:13,995
Great. Let me give you my number.
Do you have a pen?

351
00:25:14,229 --> 00:25:16,322
I don't think I have one.

352
00:25:21,236 --> 00:25:22,999
- Yes, I do.
- Great.

353
00:25:35,217 --> 00:25:37,014
And call me Allegra.

354
00:25:39,521 --> 00:25:42,319
- You're done.
- Goodbye.

355
00:25:46,061 --> 00:25:47,358
Good job.

356
00:25:50,232 --> 00:25:51,290
Oh, damn.

357
00:26:12,754 --> 00:26:17,157
She's some kind of newspaper columnist.
Comes in here once in a while. Great tipper.

358
00:26:17,259 --> 00:26:18,317
What's her drink?

359
00:26:18,427 --> 00:26:21,726
Usually beer.
Tonight, Grey Goose martini, dirty.

360
00:26:32,040 --> 00:26:33,064
Hi.

361
00:26:35,010 --> 00:26:36,705
I noticed your glass was getting low...

362
00:26:36,845 --> 00:26:39,712
so I took the liberty
of bringing you another apple martini.

363
00:26:39,848 --> 00:26:40,837
Thank you.

364
00:26:40,949 --> 00:26:44,976
And I couldn't help but notice
you look a lot like my next girlfriend.

365
00:26:45,554 --> 00:26:48,045
- What's your name?
- They call me Chip.

366
00:26:48,190 --> 00:26:50,351
You can't get them to stop?

367
00:26:51,526 --> 00:26:52,720
That was funny.

368
00:26:52,861 --> 00:26:56,353
Listen, I understand the courage it takes
to walk across a room...

369
00:26:56,465 --> 00:26:58,990
and try to generate a relationship
out of thin air.

370
00:26:59,101 --> 00:27:02,901
- So don't take the following personally.
- You have fantastic eyes.

371
00:27:04,306 --> 00:27:06,240
Thanks. Try to listen.

372
00:27:06,374 --> 00:27:10,333
This is no reflection on you.
I'm just not interested.

373
00:27:10,645 --> 00:27:13,113
But thank you for the compliment
of coming over.

374
00:27:13,248 --> 00:27:16,115
You're welcome.
So do you like Cuban food?

375
00:27:16,885 --> 00:27:20,787
Chip, seriously, that was not code for,
"I wish you'd try harder."

376
00:27:20,922 --> 00:27:25,052
Are you always so shut-down and afraid
that the right man might make you...

377
00:27:25,160 --> 00:27:27,253
Feel like a natural woman?

378
00:27:28,063 --> 00:27:31,260
Sorry I'm late, honey.
I couldn't get a cab. How was the meeting?

379
00:27:31,399 --> 00:27:35,062
Well, there was a beginning,
a middle, and an end.

380
00:27:35,504 --> 00:27:37,472
Nice to meet you, Chip.

381
00:27:42,777 --> 00:27:44,108
You, too.

382
00:27:47,182 --> 00:27:49,810
On the one hand,
it is very difficult for a man...

383
00:27:49,951 --> 00:27:52,647
to even speak to someone
who looks like you.

384
00:27:52,787 --> 00:27:55,984
But on the other hand,
should that be your problem?

385
00:27:56,124 --> 00:27:58,615
So life's kind of hard all around.

386
00:27:59,261 --> 00:28:01,593
Not if you pay attention.

387
00:28:03,431 --> 00:28:05,399
You're sending all the right signals:

388
00:28:05,500 --> 00:28:08,958
no earrings, heels under two inches,
your hair is pulled back...

389
00:28:09,104 --> 00:28:12,733
wearing reading glasses with no book,
drinking a Grey Goose martini...

390
00:28:12,841 --> 00:28:16,106
which means you had a hell of a week
and a beer just wouldn't do it.

391
00:28:16,211 --> 00:28:17,576
If that wasn't clear enough...

392
00:28:17,679 --> 00:28:21,809
there's always the "fuck off"
that you have stamped on your forehead.

393
00:28:21,950 --> 00:28:26,250
Who'd believe there's a man out there
that can sit by a woman he doesn't know...

394
00:28:26,354 --> 00:28:30,450
and genuinely be interested in who she is,
what she does, without his own agenda?

395
00:28:30,559 --> 00:28:33,494
I wouldn't even know
what that would look like.

396
00:28:33,662 --> 00:28:35,653
So what would a guy like that say?

397
00:28:35,797 --> 00:28:39,198
He'd say, "My name is Alex Hitchens
and I'm a consultant."

398
00:28:39,334 --> 00:28:41,165
But she wouldn't be interested in that...

399
00:28:41,303 --> 00:28:43,771
because she'd be counting the seconds
until he left.

400
00:28:43,872 --> 00:28:46,363
Thinking he was like every other guy.

401
00:28:46,508 --> 00:28:49,705
Which, life experience has taught her,
is a virtual certainty.

402
00:28:49,844 --> 00:28:52,642
But then he'd ask her name
and what she did for a living...

403
00:28:52,747 --> 00:28:54,942
and she might blow him off.

404
00:28:55,150 --> 00:28:56,947
Or she might say...

405
00:29:01,489 --> 00:29:05,391
I'm Sara Melas.
I run the gossip column at the Standard.

406
00:29:05,527 --> 00:29:08,496
And then he'd ask
all these penetrating questions about her...

407
00:29:08,597 --> 00:29:11,828
because he was sincerely,
if atypically, interested.

408
00:29:11,933 --> 00:29:12,991
No.

409
00:29:13,368 --> 00:29:15,802
- No?
- He'd be interested.

410
00:29:17,205 --> 00:29:19,366
But he'd see that there was no way...

411
00:29:19,507 --> 00:29:23,307
he could possibly make her realize
that he was for real.

412
00:29:23,411 --> 00:29:28,542
Well, he could be funny and charming
and refreshingly original.

413
00:29:29,384 --> 00:29:30,851
Wouldn't help.

414
00:29:30,952 --> 00:29:34,080
- Don't you hate it when that happens?
- Not really.

415
00:29:34,222 --> 00:29:37,919
They'd both probably go on
to lead the lives they were headed toward.

416
00:29:38,059 --> 00:29:40,857
My guess is they'd do just fine.

417
00:29:42,964 --> 00:29:46,024
It's a pleasure to have met you, Sara Melas.

418
00:29:51,072 --> 00:29:54,530
Grey Goose martini
from the gentleman who just left.

419
00:29:59,914 --> 00:30:01,506
Is that for me?

420
00:30:04,319 --> 00:30:05,445
What?

421
00:30:20,735 --> 00:30:22,965
Vance Munson. Sorry I'm late.

422
00:30:23,972 --> 00:30:26,873
No, not a problem.

423
00:30:28,109 --> 00:30:29,906
Wow, you're the...

424
00:30:30,845 --> 00:30:34,576
- Can I get you something to drink, Mr...
- No, I'm fine, thank you.

425
00:30:34,683 --> 00:30:36,548
So, tell me about her.

426
00:30:39,020 --> 00:30:40,715
Have you ever met someone...

427
00:30:40,822 --> 00:30:43,620
and you knew right away
she was gonna be important to you?

428
00:30:43,758 --> 00:30:47,159
Not just because of her looks,
but that X factor.

429
00:30:48,196 --> 00:30:49,720
How'd you meet her?

430
00:30:49,831 --> 00:30:53,232
Actually, I was in a shop
buying pajamas for my mom.

431
00:30:53,335 --> 00:30:55,235
And by that, of course, you mean...

432
00:30:55,337 --> 00:30:58,272
you were buying lingerie
for another woman.

433
00:30:59,641 --> 00:31:03,270
Yes. You can't help
where you meet somebody.

434
00:31:03,978 --> 00:31:06,503
And the lingerie is for a woman
I'm no longer seeing.

435
00:31:06,648 --> 00:31:09,515
But anyway, the girl I met,
the one I was talking about...

436
00:31:09,651 --> 00:31:12,347
she's so sweet, funny, Southern.

437
00:31:12,487 --> 00:31:15,513
She gives me her number.
Now she won't return my phone calls.

438
00:31:15,657 --> 00:31:19,320
I don't know what it is about her.
I just can't get her out of my mind.

439
00:31:19,461 --> 00:31:23,488
You know, food has lost its taste.
Colors, they seem dull.

440
00:31:23,631 --> 00:31:27,362
Things that used to matter...
I don't know, they just no longer do.

441
00:31:27,502 --> 00:31:30,471
I think things aren't gonna snap back
unless I...

442
00:31:32,374 --> 00:31:34,103
Unless I bang her.

443
00:31:36,311 --> 00:31:37,676
Excuse me?

444
00:31:39,414 --> 00:31:42,872
You know, bang her. Clear my head.
Get in, get off, get out.

445
00:31:45,653 --> 00:31:48,952
I think you may have misunderstood
what I do exactly.

446
00:31:49,057 --> 00:31:51,787
No, I was told you help guys get in there.

447
00:31:51,893 --> 00:31:53,827
Right. But, see, here's the thing.

448
00:31:53,928 --> 00:31:57,329
My clients actually like women.

449
00:32:00,068 --> 00:32:02,502
Hit it and quit it is not my thing.

450
00:32:02,604 --> 00:32:06,540
Let me make one thing clear to you, rabbi.
I need professional help.

451
00:32:06,674 --> 00:32:09,472
Well, that is for damn certain.

452
00:32:09,911 --> 00:32:14,473
And I'm glad you can admit it
because generally that's the hardest part.

453
00:32:17,419 --> 00:32:20,547
You see what I'm doing?
This is what I'm about.

454
00:32:21,456 --> 00:32:23,720
Power suit, power tie, power steering.

455
00:32:23,858 --> 00:32:27,885
People can wince, cry, beg,
but eventually they do what I want.

456
00:32:29,798 --> 00:32:31,891
So that's, like, a metaphor.

457
00:32:34,469 --> 00:32:37,336
Well, I'm more of a literal kind of guy.

458
00:32:37,439 --> 00:32:39,236
So when I do this...

459
00:32:41,276 --> 00:32:45,542
this is more like me saying
that I will literally break your shit off...

460
00:32:45,647 --> 00:32:48,514
if you ever touch me again. Okay, pumpkin?

461
00:32:48,616 --> 00:32:49,844
Got it.

462
00:32:57,892 --> 00:32:59,860
No.

463
00:32:59,961 --> 00:33:04,227
Pablo, I can't just mention your restaurant.
Somebody has to eat there.

464
00:33:04,332 --> 00:33:07,267
No, somebody famous. You know that.

465
00:33:07,569 --> 00:33:09,196
- Sara Melas?
- No.

466
00:33:10,104 --> 00:33:11,696
Okay. Bye.

467
00:33:13,775 --> 00:33:15,606
I need your signature.

468
00:33:29,824 --> 00:33:34,488
I hate it when a guy calls a girl
who did not give him her number.

469
00:33:34,629 --> 00:33:37,063
So this is me not calling. Over.

470
00:33:37,165 --> 00:33:40,134
Yes, you're right.
This is much less invasive.

471
00:33:40,268 --> 00:33:43,135
I've been thinking about
that sign on your forehead.

472
00:33:43,271 --> 00:33:47,264
And I was wondering if you'd mind
taking it down for dinner Friday night. Over.

473
00:33:47,709 --> 00:33:51,008
I can't. I have a couple of parties
I have to hit.

474
00:33:51,679 --> 00:33:53,340
Gossip never sleeps.

475
00:33:53,848 --> 00:33:55,839
Not till about 4:00 a.m.

476
00:33:56,351 --> 00:33:57,648
Saturday.

477
00:34:00,655 --> 00:34:02,145
I have a date.

478
00:34:03,691 --> 00:34:06,592
Do you know the definition
of "perseverance," Miss Melas?

479
00:34:06,694 --> 00:34:08,787
An excuse to be obnoxious?

480
00:34:08,963 --> 00:34:10,954
