I guess it's best just not to love at all, right?

972
01:09:02,655 --> 01:09:03,952
Or skate.

973
01:09:32,051 --> 01:09:33,518
Are you here?

974
01:09:42,561 --> 01:09:47,658
Sara, you're such an idiot! You moron!
What the hell did you think?

975
01:09:47,767 --> 01:09:50,861
You're so stupid! You gotta learn, Sara.

976
01:09:51,003 --> 01:09:53,631
- When are you gonna learn...
- Should I come back later?

977
01:09:55,841 --> 01:09:59,299
Hi. I thought you left.

978
01:09:59,545 --> 01:10:04,141
Well, I did,
but then I came back with breakfast.

979
01:10:05,084 --> 01:10:08,247
I figured it was the least that I could do.

980
01:10:09,922 --> 01:10:12,413
I didn't know what you were drinking...

981
01:10:12,792 --> 01:10:17,525
so I got a grande cap, a latte,
an Earl Grey tea...

982
01:10:17,797 --> 01:10:19,958
and something with "chai" in the title.

983
01:10:21,967 --> 01:10:23,161
Tea for me.

984
01:10:23,269 --> 01:10:25,999
Tea. Yes! I was hoping you'd say that.

985
01:10:28,974 --> 01:10:32,239
Oh, God.
You're a morning person, aren't you?

986
01:10:33,446 --> 01:10:36,677
Well, like I always tell my clients:

987
01:10:36,782 --> 01:10:39,774
Begin each day as if it were on purpose.

988
01:10:47,493 --> 01:10:49,586
- Wow. Beautiful day.
- Yeah.

989
01:10:51,297 --> 01:10:53,731
- Beautiful girl.
- Thank you.

990
01:10:55,634 --> 01:10:57,534
Well, I'm this way.

991
01:10:58,003 --> 01:11:00,369
I'm that way.

992
01:11:01,674 --> 01:11:03,869
Give me a ring sometime.

993
01:11:05,778 --> 01:11:07,575
I mean, on the phone.

994
01:11:10,182 --> 01:11:12,810
No, I definitely will.

995
01:11:15,454 --> 01:11:16,580
Good.

996
01:11:45,885 --> 01:11:47,682
I gotta go to work.

997
01:11:57,463 --> 01:11:58,589
Bye.

998
01:12:01,167 --> 01:12:02,429
Goodbye.

999
01:12:27,226 --> 01:12:30,389
Can you believe what a beautiful day it is...

1000
01:12:31,030 --> 01:12:32,292
not?

1001
01:12:32,398 --> 01:12:35,526
- What's wrong, pumpkin?
- I'm so stupid.

1002
01:12:36,202 --> 01:12:38,466
I ignored your advice. I went on that date.

1003
01:12:38,571 --> 01:12:39,595
With who?

1004
01:12:40,573 --> 01:12:42,165
Not the lingerie guy.

1005
01:12:42,274 --> 01:12:45,641
Vance Munson. And you're right,
there's no way he ever had a mother.

1006
01:12:45,778 --> 01:12:47,075
That bad?

1007
01:12:47,413 --> 01:12:51,577
He took me to Scalinatella,
and he was affectionate and sweet.

1008
01:12:52,084 --> 01:12:55,485
He told me all these intimate things,
like how he can't taste food...

1009
01:12:55,588 --> 01:12:57,078
and he wants three kids.

1010
01:12:57,223 --> 01:12:58,485
So you slept with him.

1011
01:12:59,792 --> 01:13:01,783
I never seen anybody get dressed that fast.

1012
01:13:01,894 --> 01:13:03,657
Case, I'm so sorry.

1013
01:13:05,531 --> 01:13:08,898
- Maybe I'll just die alone after all.
- No, you won't.

1014
01:13:09,034 --> 01:13:13,403
You'll meet a great guy with a great smile
and you'll travel the world together.

1015
01:13:13,539 --> 01:13:15,666
Who are you? Where's my best friend?

1016
01:13:15,774 --> 01:13:19,005
It's true. He just hasn't found you yet.
But he will.

1017
01:13:19,111 --> 01:13:22,842
Just as he's leaving, guess what he says:
"Date Doctor, my ass."

1018
01:13:22,948 --> 01:13:25,849
- What does that mean?
- It means he's really out there.

1019
01:13:25,951 --> 01:13:29,819
And if I ever meet him, the only date
he's gonna need is with a real doctor.

1020
01:13:42,468 --> 01:13:43,560
That's him.

1021
01:13:44,003 --> 01:13:46,096
Vance, is that you?

1022
01:13:46,805 --> 01:13:49,740
Yeah, hey there, beautiful.

1023
01:13:49,842 --> 01:13:51,309
Sara Melas, from the Standard.

1024
01:13:51,443 --> 01:13:53,911
I'd like to discuss
the dating consultant you hired...

1025
01:13:54,013 --> 01:13:56,174
before you went out with Casey Sedgewick.

1026
01:13:59,718 --> 01:14:03,119
You don't wanna talk, that's fine.
I'm going to write this anyway.

1027
01:14:03,222 --> 01:14:06,020
You just earned yourself a photo
with a boldface caption.

1028
01:14:06,158 --> 01:14:07,591
What? Nice.

1029
01:14:07,693 --> 01:14:11,459
I can only imagine how the trading
floor guys will react when they see this.

1030
01:14:11,563 --> 01:14:13,292
You have no proof, no facts.

1031
01:14:13,399 --> 01:14:16,129
Vance, I'm a gossip columnist, not the DA.

1032
01:14:16,235 --> 01:14:18,999
Okay, how much will it cost me
to stay out of this?

1033
01:14:19,138 --> 01:14:20,935
I don't want money. I want a name.

1034
01:14:21,040 --> 01:14:23,372
- I don't know his name.
- Well, what do you know?

1035
01:14:26,312 --> 01:14:27,711
I know this.

1036
01:14:34,086 --> 01:14:36,145
All this for a lousy lay.

1037
01:14:36,655 --> 01:14:37,952
Are we satisfied?

1038
01:14:39,692 --> 01:14:40,886
Almost.

1039
01:14:44,730 --> 01:14:47,631
No, you... You got to be...

1040
01:14:53,505 --> 01:14:54,904
Is this really necessary?

1041
01:14:55,541 --> 01:14:57,008
Have you seen your back?

1042
01:14:57,109 --> 01:15:00,909
No, but I see my front and maybe
we should be starting with some sit-ups.

1043
01:15:01,714 --> 01:15:03,341
God! Mother of Troy!

1044
01:15:06,885 --> 01:15:08,079
Hello?

1045
01:15:09,555 --> 01:15:13,355
That's crazy.
Just hearing your voice makes me smile.

1046
01:15:13,459 --> 01:15:14,756
How are you?

1047
01:15:14,893 --> 01:15:17,054
I'm good, I think.

1048
01:15:17,296 --> 01:15:20,823
No, actually, you know what?
I feel a little strange.

1049
01:15:23,035 --> 01:15:24,332
I'm good.

1050
01:15:25,738 --> 01:15:27,103
Sweet Georgia Brown!

1051
01:15:27,239 --> 01:15:28,365
What was that?

1052
01:15:28,474 --> 01:15:31,534
No, that's just some guy screaming.

1053
01:15:32,711 --> 01:15:34,542
Listen, is there any context...

1054
01:15:34,646 --> 01:15:39,743
under which you'd consider facial edema
and pharmaceutical intervention a date?

1055
01:15:41,086 --> 01:15:42,519
Probably not.

1056
01:15:42,621 --> 01:15:43,883
How about a do-over?

1057
01:15:43,989 --> 01:15:46,924
- What do you have in mind?
- Dinner, my place.

1058
01:15:47,159 --> 01:15:50,754
Because obviously going anywhere public
with you is out of the question.

1059
01:15:51,697 --> 01:15:54,461
God! That's it. I don't like you very much.

1060
01:15:54,566 --> 01:15:55,931
What is that?

1061
01:15:56,068 --> 01:15:57,262
Wait, I'm getting up.

1062
01:15:57,636 --> 01:16:00,036
It's like one of those makeover shows.

1063
01:16:00,139 --> 01:16:02,232
- That's a makeover show?
- It's Danish.

1064
01:16:02,341 --> 01:16:04,036
Almost done!

1065
01:16:05,077 --> 01:16:06,271
Friday?

1066
01:16:06,512 --> 01:16:11,245
Can't. I told a friend I'd go speed dating.
You know, for moral support.

1067
01:16:11,517 --> 01:16:13,075
But tomorrow I'm free.

1068
01:16:14,453 --> 01:16:16,387
Great. All right, 8:00?

1069
01:16:16,655 --> 01:16:17,644
Great.

1070
01:16:17,790 --> 01:16:20,588
- All right. Bye-bye.
- Bye.

1071
01:16:25,931 --> 01:16:29,128
- See, it wasn't so bad, was it?
- God!

1072
01:16:33,539 --> 01:16:36,099
Ball is back in play
after a 20-second timeout.

1073
01:16:36,208 --> 01:16:40,338
Knicks lead the Grizzlies, 12-6,
here early in the first quarter.

1074
01:16:50,155 --> 01:16:52,715
- So this is what this feels like?
- "This" being?

1075
01:16:53,358 --> 01:16:55,485
Great seats, great game.

1076
01:16:57,062 --> 01:16:58,927
Great date.

1077
01:17:01,133 --> 01:17:02,760
I mean, sort of.

1078
01:17:03,402 --> 01:17:05,734
To me, it feels like a...

1079
01:17:06,405 --> 01:17:08,430
- Date?
- Yeah.

1080
01:17:14,313 --> 01:17:16,042
Look at her. She looks so happy.

1081
01:17:16,915 --> 01:17:19,475
How does a guy like that end up
with a girl like her?

1082
01:17:25,591 --> 01:17:28,788
I am so jealous.
I've always wanted to be able to do that.

1083
01:17:29,128 --> 01:17:32,222
Really? Tonight is your lucky night.
Let's see what you got.

1084
01:17:32,331 --> 01:17:33,992
Okay. You ready?

1085
01:17:36,869 --> 01:17:40,134
- Oh, God. I'm sorry.
- It's fine.

1086
01:17:40,239 --> 01:17:42,400
Knicks off to a great start...

1087
01:17:42,541 --> 01:17:44,031
All right, here's how it works.

1088
01:17:44,143 --> 01:17:48,375
Central Park Zoo, tomorrow, noon,
by the sea lions.

1089
01:17:49,581 --> 01:17:51,208
No, don't worry. I'll find you.

1090
01:17:51,750 --> 01:17:53,547
All right. Thank you.

1091
01:18:12,137 --> 01:18:14,469
It's all right. I'm sorry.

1092
01:18:14,840 --> 01:18:16,205
Damn me.

1093
01:18:20,646 --> 01:18:23,046
That was it! You got it. Do it again.

1094
01:18:24,750 --> 01:18:26,115
Look how cute they are.

1095
01:18:57,449 --> 01:18:58,643
Thanks.

1096
01:19:15,033 --> 01:19:17,160
I had a great time tonight, Albert.

1097
01:19:18,337 --> 01:19:21,033
I had a great time, too, Allegra.

1098
01:19:41,760 --> 01:19:43,193
Good night.

1099
01:19:43,695 --> 01:19:45,026
Good night, Albert.

1100
01:19:58,710 --> 01:20:00,871
- Allegra.
- Yes?

1101
01:20:05,083 --> 01:20:06,345
Hold on.

1102
01:20:28,540 --> 01:20:30,201
I like your lips.

1103
01:20:34,313 --> 01:20:36,008
They seem to like you, too.

1104
01:20:44,489 --> 01:20:45,888
Good night.

1105
01:20:46,558 --> 01:20:47,923
Good night.

1106
01:21:24,129 --> 01:21:26,324
- Anything?
- Not yet.

1107
01:21:27,132 --> 01:21:29,623
But I got some great shots
of you biting your nails.

1108
01:21:30,035 --> 01:21:31,400
Well, it's a big story.

1109
01:21:33,372 --> 01:21:34,930
- Incoming.
- Really?

1110
01:21:35,040 --> 01:21:36,337
Yep. They're shaking hands.

1111
01:21:36,475 --> 01:21:38,807
This is so great. I can't wait to nail this guy.

1112
01:21:38,944 --> 01:21:40,935
Make sure you get a good shot of his face.

1113
01:21:41,046 --> 01:21:43,446
- What's he look like?
- Tall, dark, and handsome.

1114
01:21:43,615 --> 01:21:45,207
Basic principles:

1115
01:21:45,350 --> 01:21:47,716
No matter what, no matter who,
no matter when.

1116
01:21:47,853 --> 01:21:49,548
This is killing me.

1117
01:21:49,688 --> 01:21:51,349
Geoff is managing to play it straight.

1118
01:21:51,490 --> 01:21:53,287
How long have you been in love with her?

1119
01:21:53,392 --> 01:21:57,055
Her? About two-and-a-half years.

1120
01:21:59,731 --> 01:22:00,891
Take a look.

1121
01:22:09,007 --> 01:22:12,170
- How'd you get my card?
- Albert Brennaman.

1122
01:22:12,277 --> 01:22:14,302
- Great guy, isn't he?
- Excellent guy.

1123
01:22:16,715 --> 01:22:18,148
What? Sara.

1124
01:22:24,423 --> 01:22:27,654
- Pleasure to meet you, Geoff.
- Hey, what...

1125
01:22:32,264 --> 01:22:35,859
- How'd you get my card?
- Albert Brennaman.

1126
01:22:36,101 --> 01:22:38,262
- Great guy, isn't he?
- Excellent guy.

1127
01:22:40,605 --> 01:22:42,163
You sure you want to do this?

1128
01:22:42,908 --> 01:22:43,932
Why wouldn't I?

1129
01:22:47,446 --> 01:22:51,906
Louise made an interesting observation
on the way home the other night.

1130
01:22:53,051 --> 01:22:56,509
She said people who are guarded
are afraid...

1131
01:22:57,556 --> 01:22:59,490
that you can see right through them.

1132
01:22:59,624 --> 01:23:03,890
That's why they hide behind
layers of secrecy or humor.

1133
01:23:04,095 --> 01:23:07,462
He'll have to hide behind a lot more
than that once this hits the fan.

1134
01:23:08,233 --> 01:23:09,427
She meant you.

1135
01:23:14,773 --> 01:23:16,206
What do you want me to say?

1136
01:23:17,742 --> 01:23:21,906
That I like the guy?
Yeah, sure, I liked the guy.

1137
01:23:23,648 --> 01:23:26,082
Well, here's his shirt.

1138
01:23:28,153 --> 01:23:32,112
- Why don't you think about it? Call me.
- Thanks.

1139
01:23:43,935 --> 01:23:46,165
Papi, Sara Melas is here to see you.

1140
01:23:47,672 --> 01:23:50,732
Thanks a lot, Raoul. Send her up.
And stop calling me papi.

1141
01:24:02,521 --> 01:24:05,820
Well, aren't you a sight for sore eyes.

1142
01:24:07,125 --> 01:24:09,286
I believe this belongs to you.

1143
01:24:13,498 --> 01:24:16,126
Yeah, this thing is like a bad penny.

1144
01:24:16,234 --> 01:24:17,360
Wow!

1145
01:24:18,503 --> 01:24:19,993
So this is it.

1146
01:24:20,705 --> 01:24:22,366
Yeah, this is it.

1147
01:24:24,209 --> 01:24:26,109
Business must be good.

1148
01:24:26,745 --> 01:24:29,339
Well, it has its rewards.

1149
01:24:31,182 --> 01:24:32,513
I'll bet.

1150
01:24:33,985 --> 01:24:35,316
Tough day?

1151
01:24:36,388 --> 01:24:37,685
You could say that.

1152
01:24:39,157 --> 01:24:42,285
Well, you know what?
You can just sit back and relax.

1153
01:24:42,394 --> 01:24:44,225
I got this all covered.

1154
01:24:47,399 --> 01:24:49,890
Spanish wine!

1155
01:24:51,703 --> 01:24:54,331
How thoughtful are we?

1156
01:24:54,439 --> 01:24:57,340
- Here, let me pour that for you.
- No, that's okay.

1157
01:24:57,943 --> 01:25:00,673
- You want some?
- Sure.

1158
01:25:02,447 --> 01:25:04,574
So, Hitch.

1159
01:25:05,250 --> 01:25:08,651
Is that a noun or a verb?

1160
01:25:11,356 --> 01:25:12,618
I guess it depends.

1161
01:25:15,226 --> 01:25:19,026
Let's see, what should we toast to?

1162
01:25:22,200 --> 01:25:25,101
Never lie, steal, cheat, or drink.

1163
01:25:26,104 --> 01:25:29,301
But if you must lie,
lie in the arms of the one you love.

1164
01:25:30,241 --> 01:25:33,176
If you must steal,
steal away from bad company.

1165
01:25:33,278 --> 01:25:36,042
If you must cheat, cheat death.

1166
01:25:36,948 --> 01:25:38,313
And if you must drink...

1167
01:25:38,883 --> 01:25:42,114
drink in the moments
that take your breath away.

1168
01:25:44,389 --> 01:25:45,947
Did you just make that up?

1169
01:25:58,370 --> 01:25:59,769
Make yourself at home.

1170
01:26:00,438 --> 01:26:02,770
I'm gonna check on the risotto.

1171
01:26:04,509 --> 01:26:07,740
Look at this! Which one's the music?

1172
01:26:15,053 --> 01:26:16,850
It does lights, too?

1173
01:26:19,024 --> 01:26:21,515
Let me help you out with that.

1174
01:26:21,660 --> 01:26:24,322
Now, this is nifty.

1175
01:26:25,964 --> 01:26:27,261
What are you doing?

1176
01:26:27,732 --> 01:26:29,825
How does it work, exactly?

1177
01:26:31,469 --> 01:26:36,372
Well, usually you have dinner,
then you have dessert.

1178
01:26:37,242 --> 01:26:40,609
No, I mean your thriving business.

1179
01:26:45,050 --> 01:26:46,449
I don't do interviews.

1180
01:26:48,386 --> 01:26:52,117
But if you'd like to get back to the evening,
I'd be happy to sit and talk.

1181
01:26:52,223 --> 01:26:54,157
Great idea. You start.

1182
01:26:55,460 --> 01:26:59,988
Well, maybe I would if you weren't snarling.

1183
01:27:06,571 --> 01:27:08,539
What if I told you...

1184
01:27:08,640 --> 01:27:13,577
that I know exactly what you do
and how you do it?

1185
01:27:13,712 --> 01:27:15,612
And I think it's despicable!

1186
01:27:15,714 --> 01:27:18,547
You know what?
We might need to go out to dinner.

1187
01:27:18,683 --> 01:27:22,244
There's a great seafood restaurant
I'd love to take you to.

1188
01:27:24,289 --> 01:27:26,416
How about you just get a cleaver, butcher?

1189
01:27:26,958 --> 01:27:29,927
- Maybe I will!
- What the hell is wrong with you?

1190
01:27:30,061 --> 01:27:31,892
Nothing a front-page story can't cure.

1191
01:27:32,030 --> 01:27:33,429
So that's what this is all about?

1192
01:27:33,565 --> 01:27:36,363
Albert and Allegra
on the front of your crap-ass newspaper?

1193
01:27:36,468 --> 01:27:38,265
- You put them there!
- No, you did!

1194
01:27:38,403 --> 01:27:41,065
No, he did! The minute he called you!

1195
01:28:08,633 --> 01:28:10,692
Dr. Hitch. Listen to me, papi.

1196
01:28:10,802 --> 01:28:14,795
I need to bring my partner, Amir,
somewhere amazing for our anniversary.

1197
01:28:15,473 --> 01:28:18,374
Maybe it's not your thing, but maybe it is.

1198
01:28:18,476 --> 01:28:20,444
What the hell are you talking about, Raoul?

1199
01:28:20,578 --> 01:28:22,068
It's you, no?

1200
01:28:42,600 --> 01:28:46,559
So, my friend, how was she? Pretty good?

1201
01:28:50,675 --> 01:28:53,166
How was she? I'll tell you! She was great!

1202
01:29:07,659 --> 01:29:08,921
Isn't that the Date Doctor?

1203
01:29:09,027 --> 01:29:12,155
- I'm telling you, that's him.
- He doesn't look anything like him.

1204
01:29:12,297 --> 01:29:14,925
- Excuse me. Do you know him?
- No.

1205
01:29:15,400 --> 01:29:18,995
I want you to look me in the eye
and tell me that he did not hire you.

1206
01:29:19,137 --> 01:29:22,937
Ma'am, I have never seen this man
before in my life.

1207
01:29:23,041 --> 01:29:24,099
See you later, Tony.

1208
01:29:24,209 --> 01:29:26,803
Tony? You have got
some serious explaining to do.

1209
01:29:26,911 --> 01:29:28,879
Albert. Hitch. You all right?

1210
01:29:29,013 --> 01:29:31,811
I can't really talk right now.
I'm kind of tied up.

1211
01:29:31,916 --> 01:29:33,884
One, two. On three.

1212
01:29:41,926 --> 01:29:43,791
Women will remain seated.

1213
01:29:43,895 --> 01:29:47,058
Men will rotate to the left at the buzzer.

1214
01:29:47,365 --> 01:29:49,390
You get two minutes each,
four minutes total.

1215
01:29:49,534 --> 01:29:53,095
So trade your talk time when you hear...

1216
01:29:55,373 --> 01:29:56,567
the gong.

1217
01:29:56,708 --> 01:29:58,608
If it's mutual, you get numbers.

